The paper discusses the trend of sharing human summaries of scientific papers, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) in computer science. The focus on scientific papers suggests a connection to machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) as well. Additionally, the goal of improving automatic summarization systems suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DL (Machine Learning), followed by cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
